Example

By plotting a graph of \(y= 20x^4-4x^3-143x^2+46x+165\) find the range of values of \(x\) for which \[20x^4-4x^3-143x^2+46x+165<0\]

Solution

A software package has been used to plot the graph which is shown in the figure below. We see that \(y\) is negative when \(-2.5<x<-1\) and when \(1.5<x<2.2\).
